docs.abstract: As the new director, Cameron Shaw has developed an all-Black, all-female leadership team and is forging a five-year partnership with Mark Bradford’s nonprofit.
docs.snippet: As the new director, Cameron Shaw has developed an all-Black, all-female leadership team and is forging a five-year partnership with Mark Bradford’s nonprofit.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Cameron Shaw has had from an early age a knack for creating her own opportunities. Home from college the summer of 2002, she visited the offices of the Peter Norton Family Foundation in Santa Monica, was impressed by the very-contemporary art covering every wall, and asked if she could work there. The organization created an internship for her the following summer.

headline.main: Mapping a Bold Vision for the California African American Museum

docs.abstract: Mary J. Blige and Kendrick Lamar rounded out the set and the special guest 50 Cent surprised the crowd before Eminem knelt onstage in an apparent nod to Colin Kaepernick’s protest.
docs.snippet: Mary J. Blige and Kendrick Lamar rounded out the set and the special guest 50 Cent surprised the crowd before Eminem knelt onstage in an apparent nod to Colin Kaepernick’s protest.
docs.lead_paragraph: Dr. Dre, Snoop Dogg and Kendrick Lamar — three titans of Los Angeles rap — took the field at SoFi Stadium in Inglewood, Calif., along with Eminem (a superstar from Detroit), the singer Mary J. Blige and the special guest 50 Cent to deliver a halftime spectacular heavy on nostalgia and California pride.

headline.main: Dr. Dre, Snoop Dogg headline hip-hop halftime show as Eminem takes a knee.

docs.abstract: The mayor’s views on policing are tied in part to his relationships with families of officers killed on the job, as well as with police abuse victims.
docs.snippet: The mayor’s views on policing are tied in part to his relationships with families of officers killed on the job, as well as with police abuse victims.
docs.lead_paragraph: In his final days before taking office, Mayor Eric Adams made an unheralded visit to a Brooklyn church for a memorial service honoring two police officers killed in the line of duty seven years ago.

headline.main: How the Deaths of N.Y.P.D. Officers Have Shaped Eric Adams
headline.print_headline: How Police Deaths Have Shaped New York’s Mayor and His Policy

docs.abstract: The examinations by board-certified forensic pathologists will be available for the families of people who died in police-related circumstances.
docs.snippet: The examinations by board-certified forensic pathologists will be available for the families of people who died in police-related circumstances.
docs.lead_paragraph: A group founded by the former N.F.L. quarterback Colin Kaepernick started this week to offer free secondary autopsies for families of people who died under “police-related” circumstances.

headline.main: A Group Founded by Colin Kaepernick Is Providing Free Second Autopsies

docs.abstract: The Senate’s posturing over qualified nominees has got to stop.
docs.snippet: The Senate’s posturing over qualified nominees has got to stop.
docs.lead_paragraph: “I am an equal opportunity foe of antisemitism.” This was the assurance that Deborah Lipstadt, the renowned Holocaust scholar, offered members of the Senate Foreign Relations Committee on Tuesday in her confirmation hearing to become President Biden’s special envoy to monitor and combat antisemitism. Whatever your place on the political spectrum, she warned, if you say something that smacks of bigotry, she will call you on it.

headline.main: When Did Republicans Turn Into a Bunch of Snowflakes?

docs.abstract: The former Dolphins head coach who has accused the league and its 32 teams of discriminatory hiring practices against Black coaches will join the Steelers as a senior defensive assistant linebackers coach.
docs.snippet: The former Dolphins head coach who has accused the league and its 32 teams of discriminatory hiring practices against Black coaches will join the Steelers as a senior defensive assistant linebackers coach.
docs.lead_paragraph: Brian Flores, the former Miami Dolphins coach who is suing the N.F.L. and its 32 teams alleging discriminatory hiring practices toward Black candidates, was hired by the Pittsburgh Steelers as a senior defensive assistant/linebackers coach, the team announced on Saturday.

headline.main: Steelers Hire Brian Flores as an Assistant Amid His N.F.L. Lawsuit
headline.print_headline: The Steelers Hire Flores, Whose Lawsuit Will Continue

docs.abstract: With violent crime rates rising and elections looming, progressive prosecutors are facing resistance to their plans to roll back stricter crime policies of the 1990s.
docs.snippet: With violent crime rates rising and elections looming, progressive prosecutors are facing resistance to their plans to roll back stricter crime policies of the 1990s.
docs.lead_paragraph: Four years ago, progressive prosecutors were in the sweet spot of Democratic politics. Aligned with the growing Black Lives Matter movement but pragmatic enough to draw establishment support, they racked up wins in cities across the country.

headline.main: They Wanted to Roll Back Tough-on-Crime Policies. Then Violent Crime Surged.
headline.print_headline: Progressive Prosecutors Feel Pressure On Crime

docs.abstract: Not every killing connects with the culture and activates a mass movement. This one did.
docs.snippet: Not every killing connects with the culture and activates a mass movement. This one did.
docs.lead_paragraph: “One of the most important things that came out of this tragedy was the activation of an entire new generation of civil rights leaders.” That was part of what President Barack Obama told The Times when we asked him what the killing of Trayvon Martin, 10 years ago Saturday, meant for the United States, the movement for civil rights and for him personally.

headline.main: Trayvon Martin Is Still Making America Confront Its Original Sin
headline.print_headline: Trayvon Martin Is Still Making America Confront Its Original Sin

docs.abstract: The candidate, Craig Greenberg, was unharmed, but the attack left a bullet hole in his sweater. A man was charged with attempted murder, the police said.
docs.snippet: The candidate, Craig Greenberg, was unharmed, but the attack left a bullet hole in his sweater. A man was charged with attempted murder, the police said.
docs.lead_paragraph: A mayoral candidate in Louisville, Ky., said he was the target of a shooting inside his campaign office on Monday that left him unharmed but shaken — and with a bullet hole in the back of his sweater.
